latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hey guys welcome back to my IGTV BASICS VIDEOS
I missed creating these videos and finally I am up with the first video of this season! 
Ways to get your mascara last much longer, you can simply fake false lashes if you start repeating these steps. • I always put some olive oil before applying my mascara as this gives that extra push and prime up my eye lashes. • Never forget to remove that extra product from your spooly else you ll end up applying extra product making your eye lashes heavy and sticky • Clean Clean after you use your mascara, that’s important gurls • Never sleep with Mascara on, always use an oil based cleanser.

latestPosts.caption:
🌄 Mount Rainier One-Day Itinerary: Scenic Sights & Short Hikes

Start Early (~7:30 AM): Enter via Nisqually Entrance

⸻

1. Christine Falls (Quick roadside stop)
	•	Beautiful view right from the bridge
	•	Quick photo opportunity

2. Narada Falls (Next 10-min drive)
	•	Park and walk a short trail for a dramatic view
	•	Misty and magical!

3. Myrtle Falls (Arrive at Paradise Visitor Center)
	•	Short <1 mile walk with a stunning Rainier backdrop
	•	Easily one of the most photogenic spots

4. Skyline Trail Loop (~2.5-3 hrs, 5 miles)
	•	Start from Paradise
	•	Panoramic alpine views, wildflowers, and glaciers
	•	Don’t miss Panorama Point!

5. Ricksecker Point Scenic Drive
	•	Short one-way road with beautiful pullouts for mountain views

6. Reflection Lake
	•	Perfect mid-afternoon stop
	•	Calm waters reflect Mount Rainier — a must for photos

7. Tipsoo Lake
	•	Short drive east near Chinook Pass
	•	Gorgeous wildflowers and serene views
	•	Ideal for a relaxing walk

8. Fremont Lookout Trail (~2 hrs roundtrip, if time/energy allows)
	•	Optional, more strenuous but highly rewarding
	•	Sunset spot if you’re staying late!

latestPosts.caption:
Ever tasted the Rockies? We did—one sip at a time! Explored 5 of Manitou’s magical mineral springs, each bubbling with unique flavors and natural health perks (yes, your gut and glow will thank you). Colorado’s not just mountains and hikes—it’s nature’s own wellness bar! Between sipping springwater, soaking in the views, and biking down scenic trails, we stayed hydrated and hyped. Who knew hydration could be an adventure?

Spots:
	7 Minute Spring – Light, refreshing water with a gentle sparkle; originally a geyser that erupted every 7 minutes, now part of a sculpture park.
	Shoshone Spring – The most mineral-rich spring, known for its high sulfur content and strong “medicinal” taste.
	Navajo Spring – Historic spring behind Patsy’s; once bottled as “Manitou Ginger Champagne,” rich in minerals and carbonation.
	Cheyenne Spring – Sweet, bubbly soda spring sourced from ancient limestone aquifers over 20,000 years old.
	Iron Spring Geyser – Bold iron-rich water with a reddish hue, known for its health benefits especially for boosting iron levels.
